Home on the Range is a 1977 folk, world and country music album recorded by Slim Whitman.
An album of standards from the three genres, it reached 2 in the UK Albums Chart in 1977 staying for thirteen weeks on the charts only to be kept from the top place by 20 Golden Greats by the Supremes. It was a follow-up album to his Red River Valley, also successful in the UK in 1977.
